<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Gryfalia on 11-26-2001 09:25 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">>1) Icy servents in Sirens' Grotto. We thought it was doing huge AE dmg, it wasn't. >It had a vicious dmg shield. Once we got the dmg shield off these guys went down >easy. 

Well, they do sometimes have a damage shield, but I can guarantee you, 100%, that they DO have a killer AoE.  You will know when it hits because you will lose your first buff and take anywhere from 400 down damage (don't think I have EVER totally resisted it…resisting things in SG is kinda rare..hehe).  But when they DO have the damage shield it is VERY important to get rid of it (train your tanks to TELL YOU these things).  Hard to tell it is the DS cause he does so much AoE damage (not to mention brutal combat damage).  The secret to not getting wiped out is: 1) whatever you do kill the servant LAST.  LAST.  NOT first.  Couldn't convince the bard of this last night and led to him dying twice, and the group once.  Just keep him mezzed and get back to him.  If you don't have a mezzer of any sort and don't have a STUPIDLY high DPS, don't pull them.  ;-)  2) Stun, stun and more stun.  When we were in SG a couple nights back, it was very simple.  All classes that can stun kept chain stunning him, while the melee killed him.  In the entire session we lost exactly 2 buffs to their AoEs (i.e. they AoEd twice the whole time).  But they key is, if you don't trust your group, well, don't be there at all, but.. 

So remember that people.  Siren's Grotto is dangerous.  Don’t go there.  Trust me.  You'll hate it.  No reason to go there.  Nope, not one.  Move on, this isn't the Velketor's Labyrinth you are looking for.

As for the Damage shield question.  Shimmering Drakes (or whatever they are called) in the HoT.  They look like Chromdracs from Skyfire.  Anyway, they have a killer Damage shield and we have NEVER managed to land MoK on them, not once.  We just dispel them a ton now and hope for the best.
Gryfalia 
56 Templar of Brell (1.8 blue to go)
Imperial Guards, Druzzil Ro


